00:31:44.580 --> 00:31:49.710
I mean, I think that there is
definitely now an awareness

00:31:49.710 --> 00:31:55.100
that we move in the 20th
century from objects, artifacts,

00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:59.540
or just expressions of
beauty to narratives,

00:31:59.540 --> 00:32:01.770
that actually the
narratives of people

00:32:01.770 --> 00:32:04.650
as we move to
metropolitan cities

00:32:04.650 --> 00:32:09.030
all over the world that become
very powerful mixing places

00:32:09.030 --> 00:32:11.700
becomes very important because
the notion of how we all

00:32:11.700 --> 00:32:14.201
come together and how we make
relationships to each other

00:32:14.201 --> 00:32:16.200
is more profoundly important
in the 21st century

00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.330
than it's ever been in the
history of our humanity.

00:32:18.330 --> 00:32:20.538
Because we're now coming
closer than we've ever been,

00:32:20.538 --> 00:32:23.100
we actually spend a lot of time
getting away from each other

00:32:23.100 --> 00:32:26.920
and forming our groups how we're
like slamming back together.

00:32:26.920 --> 00:32:29.970
And so in that's sort
of coming together,

00:32:29.970 --> 00:32:32.830
where are our strands of how
we come together is critical.

00:32:32.830 --> 00:32:35.250
So I think that there's
a lot of thought

00:32:35.250 --> 00:32:38.880
about how to kind of
talk about these issues

00:32:38.880 --> 00:32:42.554
and how to also create ways
for different generations

00:32:42.554 --> 00:32:44.220
to kind of lock into
that and understand

00:32:44.220 --> 00:32:46.875
how to use that to help
them in the way they are

00:32:46.875 --> 00:32:48.500
and the kind of
metropolitan condition.

00:32:48.500 --> 00:32:49.840
I can't speak specifically
to the project you're

00:32:49.840 --> 00:32:52.048
talking about because I
don't have information on it,

00:32:52.048 --> 00:32:54.180
but I know that just
in my work that I'm

00:32:54.180 --> 00:32:58.200
doing that this is really
a big conversation.

00:32:58.200 --> 00:33:00.112
With the museum, say the--

00:33:00.112 --> 00:33:02.070
AUDIENCE: The other one
is about collaboration.

00:33:02.070 --> 00:33:04.230
DAVID ADJAYE: Oh,
collaboration, yeah.

00:33:04.230 --> 00:33:10.020
So there are 36
consultants, there

00:33:10.020 --> 00:33:13.050
are four architects
that were doing this

00:33:13.050 --> 00:33:16.080
