00:33:26.100 --> 00:33:29.190
are just too much for one
architect to work with.

00:33:29.190 --> 00:33:32.100
So we develop a
multi-headed system

00:33:32.100 --> 00:33:35.790
where my partners would
work on different aspects

00:33:35.790 --> 00:33:38.190
of the either
legislation, contract,

00:33:38.190 --> 00:33:41.790
specific ways of building,
et cetera, et cetera.

00:33:41.790 --> 00:33:44.550
And so we sort of put
ourselves into specializations

00:33:44.550 --> 00:33:46.260
and then became a
kind of team that

00:33:46.260 --> 00:33:48.570
would then deliver that thing.

00:33:48.570 --> 00:33:51.000
We didn't work on this
project with any artist

00:33:51.000 --> 00:33:53.990
specifically on the building
fabric or anything like that.

00:33:53.990 --> 00:33:57.090
That was actually
[INAUDIBLE] our job.

00:33:57.090 --> 00:34:00.840
So we were the sort of artistic
lead and the architectural lead

00:34:00.840 --> 00:34:03.030
and then we worked
with [INAUDIBLE] Group,

00:34:03.030 --> 00:34:05.870
an amazing team from North
Carolina, who delivered

00:34:05.870 --> 00:34:07.636
our delivery on the ground.

00:34:07.636 --> 00:34:10.260
And we were based in London, we
were just setting up a New York

00:34:10.260 --> 00:34:11.254
office here.

00:34:11.254 --> 00:34:13.170
The Smith Group, who
were the only people that

