00:43:20.340 --> 00:43:26.220
The dilemma of the city
is that it's not static.

00:43:26.220 --> 00:43:28.120
It's a horrible thing.

00:43:28.120 --> 00:43:30.540
But if you look at the
evolution of cities,

00:43:30.540 --> 00:43:32.910
it is permanently in flux.

00:43:32.910 --> 00:43:34.969
We are actually never static.

00:43:34.969 --> 00:43:36.510
So there's that
dilemma to deal with.

00:43:36.510 --> 00:43:38.850
So the city doesn't
belong to any generation,

00:43:38.850 --> 00:43:42.090
it's always belongs to
the future or it dies.

00:43:42.090 --> 00:43:43.780
So there's that problem.

00:43:43.780 --> 00:43:48.167
And it's a horrible one, but
it's one that one has to face.

00:43:48.167 --> 00:43:50.250
The second thing is this
notion of gentrification,

00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:54.210
which has become a bit of a kind
of easy bashing thing, people

00:43:54.210 --> 00:43:54.720
bash it.

00:43:54.720 --> 00:43:57.053
There's two things, there's
entrepreneurial opportunity,

00:43:57.053 --> 00:43:59.790
which is when
planning laws relax

00:43:59.790 --> 00:44:02.070
certain things to
activate entrepreneurs

00:44:02.070 --> 00:44:03.690
to kind of do development.

00:44:03.690 --> 00:44:04.440
That's one thing.

00:44:04.440 --> 00:44:07.860
It's actually very
controllable because the city

00:44:07.860 --> 00:44:09.824
has the power to do it.

00:44:09.824 --> 00:44:11.490
But there's this idea
of gentrification,

00:44:11.490 --> 00:44:13.420
which actually is problematic.

00:44:13.420 --> 00:44:17.190
But actually, the statistic
shows that only 10%

00:44:17.190 --> 00:44:19.524
of construction is
about gentrification.

00:44:19.524 --> 00:44:21.440
We looked into it and
we were like, oh my god,

00:44:21.440 --> 00:44:23.856
this is horrible, it's taking
over the whole [INAUDIBLE]..

00:44:23.856 --> 00:44:26.430
Then we looked at the numbers
and we were like, oh my god.

00:44:26.430 --> 00:44:29.400
It's actually these hot spots,
but they become the stories

00:44:29.400 --> 00:44:32.250
and they become the overriding
narratives that kind of blanket

00:44:32.250 --> 00:44:33.910
out everything else.

00:44:33.910 --> 00:44:37.020
So these communities don't
completely disappear,

00:44:37.020 --> 00:44:38.670
