00:45:03.475 --> 00:45:06.540
As a design, I'm
like, it doesn't

00:45:06.540 --> 00:45:09.240
work if you don't start
from history and move

00:45:09.240 --> 00:45:10.200
into the future.

00:45:10.200 --> 00:45:12.030
If you just start
in the future, it's

00:45:12.030 --> 00:45:13.297
sort of an isolated bubble.

00:45:13.297 --> 00:45:14.880
It's like a spaceship
that just lands.

00:45:14.880 --> 00:45:17.430
Spaceships are fun,
I love spaceships.

00:45:17.430 --> 00:45:19.830
But cities are a
continuum, they've

00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:22.990
been going for
10,000 years, right?

00:45:22.990 --> 00:45:25.230
That's the history of cities.

00:45:25.230 --> 00:45:28.760
It goes back to
that's the earliest

00:45:28.760 --> 00:45:30.362
that we know, about
10,000 years old.

00:45:30.362 --> 00:45:31.820
And it's a kind of
technology, it's

00:45:31.820 --> 00:45:33.690
a kind of mechanism
that continually is

00:45:33.690 --> 00:45:35.260
growing and adding to itself.

00:45:35.260 --> 00:45:38.620
So one is struggling
with this thing.

